  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive/Senior HR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Support the HR function by managing payroll, work pass applications, employee records, and recruitment processes to ensure compliance and smooth operations within a dynamic construction environment.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Process and manage payroll for over 120++ staff and workers to ensure accurate and timely salary disbursements</li><li>Administer application, renewal, and termination of work passes to maintain workforce compliance with regulatory requirements</li><li>Coordinate and submit training applications to support employee development initiatives</li><li>Maintain, update, and organize personal files and employee records to ensure data accuracy and accessibility</li><li>Arrange and coordinate interviews to facilitate effective recruitment and talent acquisition</li><li>Respond to and resolve employee and worker issues to maintain a positive workplace environment</li><li>Conduct MOM surveys and audits to ensure compliance with Ministry of Manpower regulations</li><li>Manage company PMET (Professionals, Managers, Executives, and Technicians) quota and related documentation</li><li>Prepare and submit MYE/PA applications and updates to support workforce planning</li><li>Oversee labour management activities to optimize workforce deployment and productivity</li><li>Coordinate recruitment activities to attract and onboard qualified candidates</li><li>Administer childcare leave, NS claims, and training funding claims to support employee benefits and entitlements</li><li>Prepare and submit IR8A and IR21 tax forms to comply with statutory reporting requirements</li><li>Maintain records of annual and medical leave to track employee attendance and entitlement</li><li>Prepare Letters of Appointment (LOA) to formalize employment agreements</li><li>Act as Data Protection Officer (DPO) Coordinator to ensure compliance with data privacy regulations</li><li>Assist in Temporary Occupation Licence Quota (TOLQ) matters to support project requirements</li></ul>",
